text: Helena Wiśniewska (born 18 April 1999) is a Polish sprint canoeist. She participated in the 2018 ICF Canoe Sprint World Championships where she won a medal.K-4 500 m results In 2019, she and her team won bronze in the ICF Canoe Sprint World Cup. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1999 births Category:Polish female canoeists Category:ICF Canoe Sprint World Championships medalists in kayak Category:European Games competitors for Poland Category:Canoeists at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games medalists in canoeing Category:European Games bronze medalists for Poland Category:Sportspeople from Bydgoszcz
